<title>SINGAPORE: GP Batteries Taiwan awarded ISO credit.</title>
<headline>GP Batteries Taiwan awarded ISO credit.</headline>
<dateline>SINGAPORE 1996-11-12</dateline>
<text>
<p>Battery-maker GP Batteries International Ltd said on Tuesday its Taiwan plant has been awarded the ISO 14001 accreditation on environmental management.</p>
<p>The company said in a statement it is the first battery maker in the world to receive such accreditation.</p>
<p>It said the ISO 14001 is the most important international standard within the series of ISO 14000 standards which specify the requirements of an environmental management system.</p>
<p>GP Batteries is the Singapore listed subsidiary of Hong Kong-based Gold Peak Industries (Holdings) Ltd.</p>
<p>-- Singapore newsroom (65 8703080)</p>
